                        At its heart, crowdfunding is a meeting place for creators with bold ideas and people excited to see them come to life. When you support a project, you\u2019re not just ordering a product \u2013 you\u2019re joining the journey. You\u2019ll often get early access, one-of-a-kind rewards, and the satisfaction of knowing you played a role in bringing something new into the world.
                    `)]),e._v(" "),t("div",[e._v(`
                        This guide will walk you through how crowdfunding works, so you'll know what to expect before jumping in.
                    `)])]),e._v(" "),t("div",{staticClass:"_tac"},[t("base-button",{attrs:{shape:"soft",theme:"accent"},on:{click:e.onGlossaryOpen}},[e._v("View crowdfunding glossary")])],1)]),e._v(" "),t("div",[t("base-title",{attrs:{as:"h3",level:"h2"}},[e._v("Campaign stages")]),e._v(" "),t("div",[e._v(`
                    Crowdfunding projects move through several stages, each with its own role and opportunities. Knowing what happens when will help you follow along, decide how to take part, and understand when things like pledging or sharing your shipping details come into play.
